      "content": "Valid arguments against rapid shifts often center on social equity concerns regarding displacement and gentrification. Critics argue that increased density and desirability can drive up property values, pushing out long-term, lower-income residents. Another concern involves preserving neighborhood character, as some communities feel high-density development erodes established local identities. Balancing these intense pressures—housing needs versus community stability—is the central challenge urban planners face.",
